FBIS4-12384 "drnes068_n_94002" FBIS-NES-94-068 Daily Report 6 Apr 1994 LEBANON Spanish Foreign Minister Solana Visits Spanish Foreign Minister Solana Visits Buwayz Comments on Talks NC0604184594 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1700 GMT 6 Apr 94 NC0604184594 Beirut Radio Lebanon Arabic BFN [Excerpts] At around 1915, the official Lebanese-Spanish talks ended. They were chaired on the Lebanese side by Foreign Minister Faris Buwayz. [passage omitted] The Spanish side to the talks was chaired by Spanish Foreign Minister Javier Solana. [passage omitted] Afterward, Buwayz made the following statement: [Begin recording] [Buwayz] We held a first round of talks with the Spanish foreign minister and his delegation. The talks touched on the situation in the Middle East, which is high on the list of priorities of the foreign minister's visit. We also addressed bilateral relations, in particular the economic and cultural ties between Lebanon and Spain. [passage omitted] [Correspondent] Minister, did Solana brief you on the results of his meetings in Cairo with President Mubarak and 'Arafat? And have you received any indications that the peace process is moving forward? [Buwayz] The minister's visit to Lebanon falls within the framework of a complete tour of the Middle East region. It seems he met Egyptian and Palestinian officials as well as some others. I sensed from the minister--and I hope this is true--that he is optimistic about the possibility of progress in the talks. [passage omitted] [end recording]
